President Trump awarded Tiger Woods the Presidential Medal of Freedom in a ceremony held in the Rose Garden. Trump praised Woods' achievements in golf, calling him one of the greatest athletes in the history of sports. He highlighted Woods' impact on the game of golf, his record-breaking victories, and his ability to inspire millions of people. Trump also acknowledged Woods' perseverance in overcoming injuries and personal challenges. Woods expressed his gratitude for the honor and thanked his family, friends, and supporters for their unwavering support throughout his career.